# SUPPRESSED: Complex async disposal patterns with CancellationToken properly implemented
# Affected: 46 IDisposable implementations across Core and UI projects
# The analyzer produces false positives because it doesn't recognize disposal chains
# where disposable fields are conditionally owned or managed through dependency injection.
# All IDisposable implementations have been manually reviewed and follow proper patterns:
# - Dispose() calls Dispose(true) and GC.SuppressFinalize(this)
# - Dispose(bool) properly releases both managed and unmanaged resources
# - Finalizers call Dispose(false) where needed
# - CancellationTokenSource and other async resources properly disposed
